  url = {https://tax.hawaii.gov/legal/tir/#tir2010},
  abstract = {On April 29, 2010, the Legislature overrode Governor Linda Lingle's veto of House Bill 2866 HD 1 SD 1 CD 1, which became law as Act 74, Session Laws of Hawaii 2010. Act 74 reenacts Hawaii's Estate \& Transfer Tax under Chapter 236D, Hawaii Revised Statutes (HRS), in a form that adopts conforming provisions to the Internal Revenue Code (IRC), Title 26, Subtitle B, Estate \& Gift Tax, involving two separate points in time. The mechanics of the conforming provisions is discussed in more detail below. Act 74 applies to decedents dying on or after May 1, 2010. The purpose of this Tax Information Release (TIR) is to set forth the Department's interpretation of Act 74 and to provide guidance on its application.},
